Reuters weekly polling reflected an upswing in support for President Donald Trump.  Which immediately caused them to issue an apology along with the release.

Washington, DC  The Reuters/Ipsos Core Political poll has a significant realignment this week across a number of metrics. Most pronounced is President Trumps approval rating which currently sits at 48% with all Americans. His number with registered voters is essentially the same at 49%. Corresponding with Trumps stronger approval rating, evaluations of his job performance across the board are stronger this week from 57% approving of his handling of the economy (read more)